<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>J. Milton Barnes was a Ypsilanti newspaperman and local historian.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The collection consists of sound cassettes with J. Milton Barnes reminiscing about life in Ypsilanti, Michigan during the late nineteenth and twentieth century. Topics covered include working at the Ypsilanti Press, the Opera House, the interurban train, the Barnhill Marching Band, and Michigan State Normal College (now Eastern Michigan University). The collection also includes a narrative reminiscences entitled Ypsilanti's Third Half Century covering the period from 1917 to ca. 1970.</p>
</scopecontent>

